## Rules

### BACK-001: Async/Await Pattern
severity: ERROR
scope: all I/O-bound methods in C# services
rule: All I/O-bound methods MUST use async/await. Blocking calls (`.Result`, `.Wait()`) on async methods are prohibited. Methods MUST propagate async all the way up the call chain.
threshold: max_class_lines=200, max_method_lines=40
example_correct: |
  public async Task<User> GetUserAsync(int id)
  {
      return await _repository.FindByIdAsync(id);
  }
example_incorrect: |
  public User GetUser(int id)
  {
      return _repository.FindByIdAsync(id).Result;  // blocking — prohibited
  }

### BACK-002: No Static State
severity: ERROR
scope: all C# classes
rule: Static mutable fields and static service registrations are prohibited. All services MUST be registered via dependency injection. Static helper classes MUST contain only pure functions.
threshold: max_class_lines=200
example_correct: |
  services.AddScoped<IOrderService, OrderService>();
example_incorrect: |
  public static OrderService Instance = new();  // static mutable — prohibited

### BACK-003: SOLID Interface Segregation
severity: ERROR
scope: all interfaces in the domain and application layers
rule: Interfaces MUST NOT expose methods that callers are not expected to use. Fat interfaces MUST be split into smaller focused interfaces. Implementing classes MUST NOT throw NotImplementedException.
threshold: max_method_lines=40
example_correct: |
  public interface IOrderReader { Task<Order?> GetAsync(int id); }
  public interface IOrderWriter { Task SaveAsync(Order order); }
example_incorrect: |
  public interface IOrderService
  {
      // 20 methods — not all callers need all of them
  }
